<DOCNO>GH950703-000020</DOCNO>
<DOCID>GH950703-000020</DOCID>
<DATE>950703</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Tom wants a Jag-spot</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>PHIL GORDON</BYLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>36</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>977584197</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
PARTICK THISTLE'S Inter-Toto Cup hero Tom Smith has told the club:
Stump up and I'll stay!
The 21-year-old midfielder, whose two goals dumped Keflavik at the
weekend, will meet John Lambie this week to try and thrash out a new
deal.
Smith is out of contract and only played against the Icelandic side
because he signed on for an extra month - now he wants his Firhill
future sorted out.
''I will be meeting the manager in the next few days,'' said Tom,
''but I need to wait and see if I'm offered a decent contract.
''I'd love to stay at Thistle because I enjoy playing here. My
contract finished on May 31 and I signed on for another month so I could
play in the Inter-Toto.''
Smith missed Thistle's draw in Austria with Linzer last week because
he was on holiday. Under UEFA rules he will have to sit out the clash
with French side Metz on Saturday unless he agrees to a new contract.
</TEXT>
