<TEXT>
* WE often tend to ignore events abroad which can affect our lives.
We all know about the recent European Summit. But there has been much
less attention on the American Japanese trade talks.
Yet these are of great importance to us. Japan is an enormous market.
It is not easy to penetrate - not only because of official barriers but
because the whole selling system is very inward looking.
Yes there are tax problems but it is more complex than that.
The Americans are mostly concerned about trade in cars. But if they
generally open up the Japanese market, that has to be good news for us.
Not that we completely fail at the moment in Japan. We have lots of
successful exports, mainly at the quality end of the market.
But we could do with a bigger share of such a large and prosperous
market.
</TEXT>
