<DOCID>GH950703-000034</DOCID>
<DATE>950703</DATE>
<HEADLINE>BT PLANS FREE CALLS</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>15</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>977584211</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
LOCAL phone calls could soon be free under proposals drawn up by BT to
halt the drift of customers to its rivals.
The idea, already popular in the United States, is among a series put
to industry watchdog Oftel.
Subscribers opting for free calls, which currently cost 1p per minute
at off-peak times, would pay a higher rental charge - as they do in the
U.S.
BT is losing around 50,000 customers a month, mainly to new cable
companies which offer a combined phone and television service.
The company submitted its plans to Oftel in the spring and a ruling is
due this month.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
