<DOCID>GH950703-000035</DOCID>
<DATE>950703</DATE>
<HEADLINE>IN A FROTH OVER PRICE OF PINTS</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>15</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>977584212</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
DRINK-UP while you can afford it - because the price of your pint is
going up faster than the rate of inflation.
Beer drinkers have always suspected it and now it is official says
Camra, the Campaign for Real Ale.
In Scotland a pint of beer is amongst the highest in Britain.
The survey shows real ale in Edinburgh is generally more expensive
than London.
But Paul Waterson, President of the Scottish License Trade Association
defended the prices.
He said: ''Brewers are putting the prices up while publicans are
trying to keep them down. It is making life very difficult.''
</TEXT>
