<HEADLINE>'Terrific' Liz gets vote of confidence. LAUDER LAY ON LIP GLOSS</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>15</PAGE>
<GRAPHIC>ILLUS</GRAPHIC>
<RECORDNO>977584213</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
COSMETICS giant Estee Lauder has thrown its support behind
''terrific'' Liz Hurley.
Backing for the model and actress came amid her continuing agony over
boyfriend Hugh Grant's arrest with a prostitute in Los Angeles' Sunset
Boulevard.
Company president Leonard Lauder said: ''Elizabeth Hurley's contract
with Estee Lauder remains unchanged.
''We stand by any decision Elizabeth makes in her personal life and
have not offered her any advice.
''We are supportive of Elizabeth in every way. She is terrific.''
Grant, the disgraced star of Four Weddings and a Funeral has been
charged with lewd conduct in public by LA police.
Liz's close friend, Lord Brocklehurst, today insisted: ''She is
bearing up under the stress and pressure. She has made no decision about
the future of her relationship.''
Miss Hurley fled her country hideaway near Bath, at the weekend where
she had spent the previous two days with Grant, for Sudeley Castle, in
Gloucestershire.
</TEXT>
