<DOCID>GH950703-000037</DOCID>
<DATE>950703</DATE>
<HEADLINE>ROYAL DOC QUITS NHS</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>15</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>977584214</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
PRINCE Charles' personal surgeon is quitting the National Health
Service in a fury over changes in the system.
Professor Christopher Colton, the surgeon who treated the prince when
he broke his elbow in a polo accident, said he could no longer stand the
changes in the NHS.
Many of the reforms were more to do with ''politics than patient
care'' and at one point he said he was awarded a pay increase of #20,000
for treating fewer people.
The professor is taking early retirement from his post at Nottingham
University Hospital and says he will be glad to leave the NHS.
</TEXT>
