<DOCNO>GH950703-000038</DOCNO>
<DOCID>GH950703-000038</DOCID>
<DATE>950703</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Scots beer giant pumps up profits</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>15</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>977584215</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
SCOTTISH &amp; Newcastle, which will be the UK's biggest brewer if its bid
for Courage goes through, today served up a profits jump to #264 million
despite a weakening beer market.
Stronger performances from pub catering and the Center Parcs holiday
side helped towards the pre-tax profits rise in the year to April 30
from #222 million in the previous 12 months.
S &amp; N said it had confirmed its position as a leading national pub
retailer with sales growth of 38.6 per cent to #722.7 million.
The Edinburgh-based group said profits had declined 4.7 per cent to
#82 million after margins had fallen in the off-licence trade. However,
it had strengthened its share of ''an intensely competitive market''.
</TEXT>
