<HEADLINE>Lancashire lads to the fore</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>4</PAGE>
<FLAG>SPORT</FLAG>
<RECORDNO>977584218</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
ENGLAND TEST SQUAD
MIKE Atherton has been reappointed England captain for the rest of
this summer's series against the West Indies.
Ray Illingworth, the chairman of selectors, said: ''Michael was
delighted to accept.''
Lancashire opener Atherton has led England in 20 of his 47 Tests since
succeeding Graham Gooch two years ago.
England's win at Lord's last week, levelling their six-match series
with West Indies at 1-1, was his sixth victory in charge, but Atherton
has also lost nine Tests, with five being drawn.
Illingworth said that England's selectors had formally invited
Atherton to continue during Saturday night's selection meeting in
Manchester.
It was an apt venue, since Jason Gallian, Lancashire's 24-year-old
Australian-born opener, has been called into England's squad for the
third Cornhill Test at Edgbaston next week along with his county
captain, Mike Watkinson.
Gallian will bat at No.6, unless wicketkeeper Alec Stewart does not
feel able to open after a long spell in the field. Then Gallian would go
in first along with Mike Atherton, as he does for Lancashire.
Middlesex's Mark Ramprakash has been dropped following his unhappy
pair at Lord's and scores of only four and 18 in the first Test at
Headingley.
Derbyshire all-rounder Phil DeFreitas also drops out of the squad to
make way for 33-year-old Watkinson, who has been picked because of his
ability to bowl off-spin as well as seam.
Illingworth said: ''If we feel the Edgbaston pitch is going to turn,
we might need a second spinner in the side. This squad gives us a few
options.''
Gallian, born in Sydney and a former captain of Australia Under-19s,
has Lancastrian parents and served a four-year qualification period to
become eligible for England last year.
Last winter he went to India with England A, and this summer, he has
made 537 championships runs at an average of 44.75.
Watkinson gets his first international recognition in the middle of an
outstanding season. So far he has scored 503 runs from only nine innings
at an average of 62.87. He has also taken 26 wickets, mainly with his
off-spinners at an average of 28.96. Team:
M A Atherton (Lancashire, captain) age 26, Tests 47; A J Stewart
(Surrey, wicketkeeper) 32, 47; G A Hick (Worcestershire) 29, 34; G P
Thorpe (Surrey) 25, 17; R A Smith (Hampshire) 31, 55; J E R Gallian
(Lancashire) 24, 0; D G Cork (Derbyshire) 23, 1; D Gough (Yorkshire) 24,
9; P J Martin (Lancashire) 26, 2; R K Illingworth (Worcestershire) 31,
4; A R C Fraser (Middlesex) 29, 25; M Watkinson (Lancashire) 33, 0.
</TEXT>
