<DATE>950703</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Sturrock signs up defender</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>7</PAGE>
<FLAG>SPORT</FLAG>
<RECORDNO>977584219</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
ST Johnstone last night dived into the transfer market by signing
Dundee right back John McQuillan.
Saints wanted to sign McQuillan before last season's transfer
deadline, but were frightened off by the asking price of #100,000.
Now manager Paul Sturrock hopes to reach an agreement with Dundee over
a fee and avoid going to a tribunal.
Ironically, McQuillan will make his competitive debut for his new club
against Dundee in the opening league game of the season at McDiarmid
Park on August 12.
Saints are now able to field a new full-back partnership, as Sturrock
recently signed Stenhousemuir left back Euan Donaldson for #80,000.
Meanwhile, former Falkirk and St Mirren defender Roddy Manley, who has
just returned from a spell in Hong Kong, will train with Dundee this
week and is almost certain to join them if he proves his fitness.
But Polish star Dariusz Adamczuk, the player at the centre of a
transfer tangle for the last year, has rejected the chance of returning
to Dundee on a year's contract.
* BARCELONA have transferred Bulgarian striker Hristo Stoichkov to
Italian club Parma in a deal reported to be worth $15m, half of which
will go to the player.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
