<TEXT>
DINGWALL'S David Barnetson set a second-division high jump record of
2.17 metres for Edinburgh Southern in the men's Guardian Assurance
British League meeting at Crawley.
But Southern could finish only fifth on the day and are now last
overall, two points behind Crawley.
Elliot Bunney, the former Scottish champion and Olympic relay silver
medallist, had his first individual outing of the season in the B 100
metres finishing third behind Toby Box in 11.0sec.
Edinburgh AC improved their position slightly by finishing third in
the fourth division at Meadowbank, where Doug Walker picked up the Man
of the Match award.
Walker, coming back after a month out through injury, won the 100m in
10.79 and the 200 in 21.49, both times achieved in spite of headwinds.
Stephen Hayward won the shot (15.08m) and discus (46.94m) while Darren
Ritchie won the long jump with a wind-assisted 7.33m.
The capital side are now fifth overall but only one point ahead of
Leeds City.
* COMMONWEALTH Games internationalist Ross Low (Red Star AC) won the
100m and 200m wheelchair races in the Scottish Handicapped Grand Prix at
Meadowbank, recording times of 18.07sec and 30.65 respectively.
Clubmate Karen Lewis set a Scottish record of 41.73sec for the 200m
event with an easy victory over her rivals.
