<TEXT>
ANNIKA Sorenstam completed an impressive second European victory in
three weeks yesterday and gave Sweden its fifth consecutive win in the
Hennessy Cup at Refrath, Cologne.
Sorenstam, winner in Austria last month, finished with a 68 for a
17-under-par 271 to take the #45,000 first prize. She was one stroke
ahead of Britain's Trish Johnson, who shared second place with British
Open champion Lotta Neumann, another Swede.
Gillian Stewart was the best of the Scottish trio. A final round of 72
