<TEXT>
BRITISH riders flopped disastrously at Aachen yesterday as Jean-Claude
Vangeenberghe won the Grand Prix at the German event.
The 32-year-old Belgian, riding Omnistor Freestyle, came out top in a
nine-horse timed jump-off which none of the British hopefuls could
reach.
Michael Whitaker came nearest, but a second round mistake on Midnight
Madness kept him out of the jump-off and left him in 12th place.
Team-mate Nick Skelton, who posted a double clear on Dollar Girl in
the team effort, went out after an opening round error on the same
partner. Geoff Billington also went out with a single mistake on It's
Otto.
Vangeenberghe's third clear in 50.34secs earned him the first prize of
around #32,000, ahead of Frenchman Herve Godignon, who was 0.14s slower
on Twist du Valon. Results:
