<TEXT>
JIM Gallagher surrendered a three-shot lead before fighting back to
clinch a dramatic victory at the $1.25m St Jude Memphis Classic in
Memphis, Tennessee, yesterday.
He sank a 10-foot par-saving putt on the final hole to eke out a
one-stroke win over fellow Americans Jay Delsing and Ken Green.
Gallagher seemed in command until he double-bogeyed the twelfth hole
and bogeyed the thirteenth on the Southwind TPC course to let his
pursuers back into the hunt.
However, five closings pars was all Gallagher needed to clinch his
fifth US Tour victory, and his second of the year, after a closing
one-over-par round of 72.
He finished at 17-under 267 to collect 216,000 and jump to eleventh in
the US Ryder Cup standings. The top 10 players after next month's US PGA
Championship automatically make the American team.
''My putter's what kept me in there all week and it saved me at the
end,'' said Gallagher.
Delsing tied Gallagher with two holes left, but he bogeyed the
seventeenth and narrowly missed a birdie putt at the last. Final
