<HEADLINE>Has Socialism failed?</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>10</PAGE>
<ARTICLETYPE>CORRESPONDENCE</ARTICLETYPE>
<RECORDNO>977584286</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
CAN anyone tell me why everyone seems to assume that Socialism has
failed? Where did we ever have Socialism?
Certainly not in Soviet Russia as James Burnham showed many years ago
in his book The Managerial Revolution.
We have had the Labour Party in power in this country but they were
working with a capitalist system. Has there ever been Socialism in any
country?
Those who believe that private enterprise is superior to public
enterprise are appealing to human greed to produce more and more goods
in the belief that human happiness depends on havingness.
If more goods are what is wanted, why can't Socialism produce the
goods? Is it because it isn't based on greed? Is it desirable that we
must be greedy to get what we want?
Values are all important. Is the desire to have more a good human
value?
Jack Angus,
176 Great George Street,
Glasgow.
</TEXT>
