<HEADLINE>Letting M Chirac know</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>10</PAGE>
<ARTICLETYPE>CORRESPONDENCE</ARTICLETYPE>
<RECORDNO>977584287</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
THE decision of the President of France to resume nuclear tests in the
South Pacific is shocking. Shocking to all who are committed to the
success of the Nuclear Non-proliferation Treaty and a Comprehensive Test
Ban Treaty; shocking to all who fear the possible damage to the
ecological balance of the planet, damage which simply cannot be
calculated; and shocking to those who live in the South Pacific and to
all who care about them.
President Chirac is new to power: he needs to know how deeply many
people feel. His address is President Chirac, Palais de L'Elysee, Paris.
Rev Andrew R C McLellan,
Convener, Church and
Nation Committee,
Church of Scotland,
121 George Street,
Edinburgh.
</TEXT>
