<TEXT>
AJACCIO: A French ferry strike which halted crossings to the holiday
island of Corsica for almost four days has been called off after unions
won job security pledges from the state-owned ferry operator. Officials
of the communist-led CGT union said crews had voted to go back to work.
Thousands reached the island yesterday after driving along the Riviera
coast to Italy and queueing overnight for places on ferries from Genoa.
