<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>7</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>977584306</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
BAGHDAD: The UN official in charge of destroying Iraq's weapons of
mass destruction said yesterday Iraq had provided missing information on
its suspected biological weapons programme. ''The Iraqi government has
provided new information with regard to biological weapons and we will
assess that information and report about it to the Security Council,''
Rolf Ekeus said.
