<TEXT>
BANGKOK: Thai voters have swept Prime Minister Chuan Leekpai's
government from office and given the main opposition party, led by
Banharn Silpa-archa, a chance to head a new coalition, local media
reported from polling stations. Banharn claimed victory early on Monday,
telling reporters he planned to form a six-party coalition government
following Sunday's general election.
