ADDIS ABABA: Ethiopian security forces shot dead three gunmen who had
been on the run since their failed attempt to assassinate Egyptian
President Hosni Mubarak, officials said. Ethiopian television said the
shoot-out in which two Ethiopian security men were wounded took place in
an area of the capital Addis Ababa.
