<TEXT>
MOSCOW: Russian President Boris Yeltsin's government comfortably
survived a confidence vote in a move which defused a political crisis in
Moscow and helped peace talks in war-torn Chechnya. In the devastated
Chechen capital Grozny the chief Chechen negotiator at the peace talks
said rebels would destroy some of their heavy weapons in a goodwill
