<TEXT>
KARACHI: At least 10 people, including a policeman, were killed and 16
wounded yesterday in the latest outbreak of ethnic violence in the
sprawling Pakistan port city of Karachi, police said. The new deaths
bring the toll to 29 in two days and to around 950 so far this year. In
1994 about 800 people died in communal violence.
