<DOCNO>GH950703-000176</DOCNO>
<DOCID>GH950703-000176</DOCID>
<DATE>950703</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Lottery Fund gives #300,000 to benefit sports in Scotland</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>CALUM MACDONALD</BYLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>6</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>977584354</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
FOURTEEN sports clubs and organisations across Scotland today benefit
in the latest round of grants from the Lottery Fund, worth a total of
almost #300,000.
The fund, administered by the Scottish Sports Council, is to pay out
nearly #50,000 to the Scottish Parachute Club, based near Auchterarder,
for the purchase of a 10-seater plane, to be used by its 800 members.
A similar grant is being awarded to Glasgow Rowing Club, to help it
build a new boathouse and clubhouse.
Mr Graeme Simmers, chairman of the Scottish Sports Council, said: ''I
am delighted that a full range of sports are benefiting, reflecting the
diversity of interest across sport in Scotland.''
Today's awards are the fifth set from the fund since it started
operating in March. Grants totalling #5,357,746 have gone to 48
projects.
The other recipients are:
Dullatur Community Council, Cumbernauld: #36,300 to help provide a new
pavilion, upgrade two tennis courts and build two new all-weather
courts.
Anchor Bowling Club, Renfrew: #35,000 to help the club retain its
ground and facilities.
Forth Area Federation of Anglers: #24,000 to provide a new boathouse
and amenity block with toilets, washing facilities, heating and
lighting.
Hawick Rugby Club: #19,600 to help construct two extra changing rooms
with shower facilities and toilets.
Clarkston Rugby Club, Giffnock: #19,500 to install drainage for three
pitches.
Castle Tennis Club, Dunoon: #10,900 to provide a fast-draining
artificial surface for two new tarmac courts.
C R Cats Canoeing Club, Alva: #9300 to help fund the building of a
regional canoe slalom training and competition site.
Skeabost House Hotel, Skye: #8000 to restore the environment around
the River Snizort, which used to be one of the most prolific salmon
rivers in Scotland.
Forfar Sailing Club: #6000 towards acquiring training dinghies and
storage facilities.
Clydesdale Amateur Rowing Club: #5390 to help buy a beginners' boat
and lightweight boats suitable for women and juniors.
Glenshiel and Kintail Gun Club, Dornie: #4900 to help provide six clay
target shooting launchers and provide pathways to help wheelchair users.
St Duthus Bowling Club, Tain: #1300 to build artificial banks for the
club's outdoor bowling green.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
