<HEADLINE>Three held over death</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>1</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>977584369</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
THREE men were arrested early this morning in connection with the
death of a 40-year-old man in Leith, Edinburgh, at the weekend.
Mr Patrick O'Connor died after an incident in the city's Pitt Street
on Saturday night.
The dead man was known to have been in The Granary public house in
Ferry Road shortly before the incident.
A report has been sent to the procurator-fiscal.
